This paper deals with the computation of equilibria in extensive-form games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes algorithms for computing these equilibria, which involves optimization and computational complexity (cs.AI). The algorithms are based on the ellipsoid method, which is a technique in convex optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the hardness of the problem in general multi-player games, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes a practical algorithm for solving the problem, which involves machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
